tify gaps in processes, systems or resources that may hinder the business development. Make timely and informed decisions based on thorough analysis, assessment, and markets trend and research.\n• Innovate on new ways to leverage our unique data assets to create new analytics services and products.\n• Managing large scale migration of clients onto the new platform owning segmentation of clients to be onboarded.\n\nRequired qualifications, capabilities, and skills:\n• Understanding of how to use data to drive business value leveraging a range of analytical tools (e.g. SQL, Python)\n• Demonstrated experience in managing/deploying AI/ML models at scale and in the use of data visualization tools and data analysis software.\n• Adept use of business intelligence and data visualization tools such as Tableau/Alteryx.\n• Experience in a team lead role within a data-driven organization and track record of working with cross-functional teams, including data scientists, engineers, and business stakeholders.\n• Excellent communication skills, with the ability to explain complex data concepts to non-technical stakeholders.\n• Proven experience as a Digital Product Manager in banking or financial industry.\n• Analytical mindset to ensure we commercialize the products that deliver value.\n• Quick learner with excellent attention to detail and strong work ethic',
