    'description': 'As a Senior Product Manager - User Onboarding reporting to our Director of Product, you will be responsible for evolving and improving one of our key areas in TransferGo - Customer Journeys. This entails the translation of product value into quantitative terms. Together with Compliance, Marketing, other Product & Engineering teams you will be creating the strategy and executing product development to enable stakeholders with customisable features and providing our customers with best onboarding experience in the market. Our product is about providing seamless registration and onboarding experience while staying compliant.\n\nHere’s what you’ll be doing:\n\nBuilding product roadmaps, strategy and vision\n\nYou’ll be responsible for building a product roadmap while making use of data from secondary/primary research and requirement gathering, product analytics, competitor comparison, and other relevant business information. Additionally, we expect you to identify risks, challenges... opportunities and business integration needs and translate those into actionable deliverables. You will be owning a discovery track with multiple discovery items in parallel that touches and overlaps with other product areas.\n\nPartnering with different level stakeholders\n\nYou’ll be working closely with C level executives, directors, engineering managers, other product managers and vendor’s delivery teams who will help to drive achieving key targets. You will spend your day-to-day working with software engineers who’ll help facilitate product development, drive and ensure alignment across multiple teams. You will partner a lot with Compliance, Marketing and other stakeholders to create amazing user experience.\n\nLeading with ambition\n\nYou’ll be leading the team towards the success of the project while setting up target KPIs and pursuing OKRs. Together with your engineering manager you will be in charge of product deliveries and solutions that highly skilled develo