    'location': '  London, UK   ',
    'via': 'via Thomson Reuters Careers',
    'description': "We are looking for a Product Manager to help us evolve our portfolio of products for the next generation, with an initial focus on our pictures (photography) services. From concept to market launch and beyond, the candidate will be a key member of our multi-disciplined team, ensuring every aspect of the products they lead delights our global customer base by being the best it can be.\n\nOur products and services are routinely used by many of the world’s largest media brands to tell their stories. The successful candidate will be responsible for working with customers across the globe to determine their needs and translate them into viable and compelling products which improve customer experience and drive growth. Close collaboration is also needed with internal stakeholders, including technology, finance, sales, marketing and editorial colleagues.\n\nOur product team come from a range of backgrounds: from editorial, to design, technology, data analytics, and commercial; what unifies them... is the desire to constantly innovate to create the best possible holistic experience for our customers.\n\nWe are looking for someone who is inspired by the idea of applying their product management expertise to build the next generation of reliable, trusted news & information services.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nAs our Product Manager you will:\n• Act as product manager for key Reuters products (initial focus will be on Reuters Pictures photography products).\n• Create and execute a compelling vision for the future direction of our pictures (photography) product, with a particular focus on the opportunities & implications created by new and emerging technologies, especially artificial intelligence.\n• Lead the development, launch, and all aspects of the product life-cycle for these products.\n• Conduct qualitative and quantitative analysis to determine the overall health of products and identify new opportunities for improvements, new ways of working, and new areas of development.\n• Work with editorial, technology, legal, customer support, and other teams to ensure that our practices, templates, and procedures make us easy to do business with.\n• Plan & deliver features with an end-to-end approach: from camera through to customer (encompassing production systems, back-end processing, distribution platforms & front-end UI elements).\n• Manage exceptions and unexpected changes to our product portfolio and operations.\n• Work with the wider Thomson Reuters organization to develop, support and ensure adherence to corporate level best practices.\n\nKey Relationships:\n• Customers (especially publishers, news organizations, and digital platforms)\n• Sales, distribution and business development teams\n• Technology development team\n• Reuters photographers and other editorial teams\n• Suppliers\n• Legal staff\n\nAbout the Role\n\nYou're a fit for the Product Manager if you have:\n• Significant experience in a relevant role, either directly as a product manager, or working in a similar cross-functional capacity, ideally in a news, media, digital, data, technology or rights management business.\n• Creative thinking skills, ability to make connections, find patterns and use their imagination to create the best possible customer experience.\n• General knowledge of, and genuine interest in the photography, news & media industries and how trends and practices differ globally.\n• Must have maturity, poise, and communication skills suitable to interact directly and build trust with high-profile customers and partners.\n• Proven ability to influence cross-functional teams without formal authority.\n• Ability to establish and manage 3rd party relationships including suppliers and collaboration partnerships.\n• Prioritization and multi-tasking skills are essential.\n• As our business is built on trust, a strong sense of ethics and ability to communicate precisely are required for this role.\n\nDesired Skills:\n• Strong product management skills, e.g. direct experience in areas such as creating a compelling product vision, customer requirement analysis, roadmaps, user experience design, etc.\n• Experience in working closely with technology development teams, especially in an agile software development environment.\n• Experience in developing products in AI & machine learning related areas.\n• Ability to use data and analytics to set key success metrics and monitor product performance.\n• Ability to develop business cases that support decision making, e.g. in ‘buy vs. build’ scenarios.\n• Proficiency in more than one language would be a benefit.\n• University degree or equivalent experience in related field(s) preferred.\n\nWhat’s in it for You?\n\nAt Reuters, our people are our greatest assets. Here are some of the benefits we offer for your personal and professional growth:\n• Global Career: As a global company, we can offer a truly international career and progression opportunities.\n• Learning & Development: On the job learning and coaching. We also have a dedicated training team focused on the continuous development of our journalists.\n• Benefits: We offer competitive salary packages and market leading benefits including paid volunteering days.\n• Perks: Work alongside Pulitzer Prize-winning journalists and a team who provide unmatched, award-winning coverage of the world’s most important stories.\n\nAbout Reuters\n\nReuters is the world’s largest multimedia news provider. Founded in 1851, it is committed to the Trust Principles of independence, integrity and freedom from bias. With unmatched coverage in over 16 languages, and reaching billions of people worldwide every day, Reuters provides trusted intelligence that powers humans and machines to make smart decisions. It supplies business, financial, national and international news to professionals via desktop terminals, the world's media organizations, industry events and directly to consumers.\n\nReuters: The Real World in Real Time.\n\n#LI-KK1\n\nDo you want to be part of a team helping re-invent the way knowledge professionals work? How about a team that works every day to create a more transparent, just and inclusive future? At Thomson Reuters, we’ve been doing just that for almost 160 years. Our industry-leading products and services include highly specialized information-enabled software and tools for legal, tax, accounting and compliance professionals combined with the world’s most global news services – Reuters. We help these professionals do their jobs better, creating more time for them to focus on the things that matter most: advising, advocating, negotiating, governing and informing.\n\nWe are powered by the talents of 26,000 employees across more than 70 countries, where everyone has a chance to contribute and grow professionally in flexible work environments that celebrate diversity and inclusion. At a time when objectivity, accuracy, fairness and transparency are under attack, we consider it our duty to pursue them. Sound exciting? Join us and help shape the industries that move society forward.\n\nAccessibility\n\nAs a global business, we rely on diversity of culture and thought to deliver on our goals. To ensure we can do that, we seek talented, qualified employees in all our operations around the world regardless of race, color, sex/gender, including pregnancy, gender identity and expression, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, disability, age, marital status, citizen status, veteran status, or any other protected classification under applicable law. Thomson Reuters is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer providing a drug-free workplace.\n\nWe also make reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and for sincerely held religious beliefs in accordance with applicable law.\n\nProtect yourself from fraudulent job postings click here to know more.\n\nMore information about Thomson Reuters can be found on https://thomsonreuters.com",
